# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: basque-pelota-world-championships
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/1952-basque-pelota-world-championships] The **1952 Basque Pelota World Championships** were the 1st edition of the Basque Pelota World Championships organized by the FIPV.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/1952-basque-pelota-world-championships] A total of 17 events were disputed, in 5 playing areas.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/1955-basque-pelota-world-championships] The **1955 Basque Pelota World Championships** were the 2nd edition of the Basque Pelota World Championships, organized by the FIPV.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/1955-basque-pelota-world-championships] A total of 12 events were disputed, in 4 playing areas.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/1958-basque-pelota-world-championships] The **1958 Basque Pelota World Championships** were the 3rd edition of the Basque Pelota World Championships organized by the FIPV.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/1962-basque-pelota-world-championships] The **1962 Basque Pelota World Championships** were the 4th edition of the Basque Pelota World Championships organized by the FIPV.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/1966-basque-pelota-world-championships] The **1966 Basque Pelota World Championships** were the 5th edition of the Basque Pelota World Championships organized by the FIPV.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/1970-basque-pelota-world-championships] The **1970 Basque Pelota World Championships** were the 6th edition of the Basque Pelota World Championships organized by the FIPV.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/1974-basque-pelota-world-championships] The **1974 Basque Pelota World Championships** were the 7th edition of the Basque Pelota World Championships organized by the FIPV.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/basque-pelota-world-championships] The **Basque Pelota World Championships** is a quadrennial tournament first organized in 1952 by the International Federation of Basque Pelota.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/basque-pelota-world-championships] The modern championships crown the best amateur players in fifteen different playing categories.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/basque-pelota-world-championships] The first edition of the tournament was organized in 1952 and until 1958 was played every three years.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/basque-pelota-world-championships] The tournament has occurred every four years since then.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/basque-pelota-world-championships] No third place titles were awarded during the first five editions of the tournament.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/basque-pelota-world-championships] Additionally, the number of disciplines disputed at each tournament has varied depending on the edition and has even included disciplines played on the Plaza Libre in 1952 and 1958.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/basque-pelota-world-championships] Until the edition of 1990, no women's categories were disputed in the championships.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/basque-pelota-world-championships] A single women's discipline was added in 1990 (Paleta goma – Trinquete), then another one in 1994 (Frontenis), and finally a third one in 2014 (Paleta goma – Fronton 30 m), bringing the total number of disputed categories to fifteen.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/basque-pelota-world-championships] Starting in 1995, the FIPV has also organized a Basque Pelota World Cup on each of the four categories of Basque pelota (Trinquete, Fronton 30m, Fronton 36m, Fronton 54m) which are also played quadrennially.
[src:basque-pelota-world-championships/basque-pelota-world-championships] No bronze medals were disputed from 1952 to 1966.
